LOCATION:The Ostrom Workshop\, 513 N PARK AVE - Room Number: Tocqueville
GEO:39.171057;-86.524959
SUMMARY:Environmental Impacts of Tech Working Group Round Table
DESCRIPTION:This roundtable marks the launch of a new\, cross-campus work
 ing group focused on the environmental impacts of digital and emerging te
 chnologies. The session will bring together faculty\, researchers\, and s
 taff from across disciplines to share perspectives\, connect ongoing effo
 rts\, and identify opportunities for collaboration.  The discussion will 
 explore how technologiesâ€”such as data centers\, digital infrastructure\
 , and emerging tech systemsâ€”intersect with environmental concerns inclu
 ding energy use\, water\, materials\, waste\, governance\, and resilience
 . Participants will also consider how a coordinated working group can sup
 port interdisciplinary research\, seed new collaborations\, and respond t
 o funding opportunities.  The event will be informal and interactive\, wi
 th time for networking\, discussion\, and idea generation. All interested
  in environmental\, technological\, policy\, or governance dimensions of 
 these challenges are encouraged to attend. Meeting URL: https://teams.mic
 rosoft.com/meet/21610994102825?p=pxPvwyCygmOyrmOiye
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  This roundtable marks the launch of a n
 ew\, cross-campus working group focused on the environmental impacts of d
 igital and emerging technologies. The session will bring together faculty
 \, researchers\, and staff from across disciplines to share perspectives\
 , connect ongoing efforts\, and identify opportunities for collaboration.
 </p><p>  The discussion will explore how technologiesâ€”such as data cent
 ers\, digital infrastructure\, and emerging tech systemsâ€”intersect with
  environmental concerns including energy use\, water\, materials\, waste\
 , governance\, and resilience. Participants will also consider how a coor
 dinated working group can support interdisciplinary research\, seed new c
 ollaborations\, and respond to funding opportunities.</p><p>  The event w
 ill be informal and interactive\, with time for networking\, discussion\,
  and idea generation. All interested in environmental\, technological\, p
 olicy\, or governance dimensions of these challenges are encouraged to at
 tend.</p> Meeting URL: https://teams.microsoft.com/meet/21610994102825?p=
 pxPvwyCygmOyrmOiye
