SUMMARY:Agentic AI Strategies and Applications
DESCRIPTION:Cohort 1:&#160\;June 23 to July 14\, 2026 from Noon to 1:30pm
  ET every TuesdayDelivery: Fully online. Pre-recorded content available o
 n demand\; live sessions held via Zoom at scheduled times. Live sessions 
 will be recorded if you cannot attend during the scheduled time.Program F
 ormat: Approximately 12 hours total\, delivered over 4 weeks (one module 
 per week). Each week includes ~1.5 hours of pre-recorded content\, one au
 to-graded quiz\, and one 90-minute live online session.  Kelley faculty a
 nd industry experts will lead you through real-world business cases\, sim
 ulations\, and hands-on low/no-code exercises as you build the ability to
  identify opportunities\, develop agentic workflows\, and evaluate outcom
 es based on business impact.  Agentic AI Strategies and Applications is d
 esigned to equip you with practical skills to immediately improve product
 ivity using AI. This program focuses on autonomous AI agentsâ€”systems th
 at can take goals\, break them into steps\, use tools\, and get work exec
 uted with minimal human intervention.  The program begins with essential 
 foundations in modern AI and foundation models (including large language 
 models that power agentic workflows)\, presented in an accessible way for
  non-technical professionals. From there\, you will learn to map workflow
 s\, select the right tools\, and translate complex problems into structur
 ed agentic solutions.  The Kelley Agentic AI Certificate Program will be 
 designed and delivered by faculty whose combination of current agentic AI
  instruction\, applied industry experience\, and executive level teaching
  clearly differentiates Kelley from other potential providers. Together\,
  the faculty ensure the program reflects both how agentic AI is shaping b
 usiness today and how professional teams can apply it to build real solut
 ions and drive measurable productivity gains.Global Authority in Enterpri
 se AI Strategy: Dr. Sagar Samtani is a preeminent global expert in applie
 d AI and cybersecurity. In 2024-2025\, he served as the Director of the A
 I for Business Intelligence Research Center at Taiwan Semiconductor Manuf
 acturing Company (TSMC)\, the world's most critical semiconductor manufac
 turer. His unique background in guiding enterprise-wide AI strategies for
  global leaders ensures that this program delivers insights into connecti
 ng AI innovation with large-scale business intelligence and secure operat
 ional workflows.Pioneering Research in Autonomous Systems: Dr. Jinjing Zh
 ang is a leading agentic AI researcher focused on the intersection of hum
 an decision-making and autonomous systems. As the architect of the #1-ran
 ked Kelley Direct MBA course on Agentic AI\, she brings cutting-edge fram
 eworks for governance\, autonomous deployment\, and enterprise-scale use 
 cases.Week 1 â€” Foundations: What AI is and how it evolved\; non-technic
 al introduction to large language models\; chatbot vs. agent\; identifyin
 g AI use cases in your organizationWeek 2 â€” Autonomous Agents: How auto
 nomous agents work\; delegating tasks with context\, instructions\, and g
 uardrails\; evaluating agent output and knowing when to override\; live d
 emo building an autonomous agentWeek 3 â€” Building Agentic Systems: How 
 agents use tools and connect to external systems\; knowledge grounding an
 d giving agents access to your data\; memory and multi-step workflows\; l
 ive demo of an end-to-end agentic workflowWeek 4 â€” Enterprise Reality: 
 Deploying agentic AI in organizations\; governance\, security\, and priva
 cy considerations\; measuring ROI and business impact\; wrap-up discussio
 nCertificate and Digital Badge: Awarded upon completing all pre-recorded 
 modules\, passing all weekly quizzes\, and participation in the live (and
  on-demand) sessions.Discount pricing is available for IU staff\, student
 s and alumni\, as well as partners and companies sending three or more pa
 rticipants. Contact us at kelleypd@iu.edu (mailto:%20kelleypd@iu.edu) for
  related discount codes to apply at check out.
